- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses the computational complexity of the problem and presents a bilinear program characterization. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the behavior of Markov Chains, which can be modeled using programming languages. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the behavior of Markov Chains, which can be used to model and analyze control systems.
